CAPE TOWN &#8211; Three security guards have been shot and wounded in Browns Farm in Philippi.The guards were accosted by three men while protecting municipal workers along Link Road.The police&#8217;s Frederick van Wyk said: All the firearms were taken by the suspects and the guards were rushed to a nearby hospital for medical treatment. Cases of attempted murder and armed robbery have been opened for investigation. A South African Police Service van at a crime scene. Picture: Twitter/@SAPoliceService.Source: EWN!